  <bioghist id="aspace_9e18be4f7574e04c258f76214e280c39">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>The Natural History Society is also called the Jordani Club, in honor of David Starr Jordan, a former Cornell biologist.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_1242c7531a2b01d5dcae6c4b6fea3413">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Minute books (1876-1898), ledger, containing the Society's constitution with amendments, and a membership list which gives some information about some of the individual members; correspondence, publicity, accounts, photographs, and other manuscripts.</p>  </scopecontent>
